## Widget instructions

- This loop owns a widget: a small HTML tile on the user's Jaz board, updated by you on every run.
- Build it as a polished Jaz artifact that happens to publish into a board tile, not as a bare status snippet.
- Before creating or materially changing the tile, call `visualise:read_me` from the `jaztools` MCP server. Use the closest module (`chart`/`data_viz` for metrics, `mockup` for UI/status surfaces, `diagram` for flows).
{{- if .FilePath}}
- Widget file: {{.FilePath}} — create or overwrite it this run, then publish it.
{{- end}}
- Your widget workspace is the widget file. There are no companion, guide, or metadata files to find or maintain — title and size_hint are publish parameters, not files. Other directories under the automations root belong to other loops; never read or mirror their widgets.
- Write a self-contained HTML fragment (no <!doctype>, <html>, <head>, or <body>), under 1 MB. It lives outside the session workspace; if a file tool refuses the path, write it via the shell (like the memory file).
- Tile quality floor: fill the available tile with one stable root container; use scoped CSS, clear hierarchy, deliberate spacing, and finished visual styling; avoid fixed positioning, viewport units, clipped overflow, placeholder text, and dead empty regions. Use one internal scroll region only when the data genuinely needs it.
- For news, status, or tracker loops, design for a glance: put the strongest 2-4 signals first, use compact rows/chips/metrics, and avoid a long stack of article cards or prose paragraphs.
- Keep it read-only and show only the data the user asked the loop to track. The board chrome already shows the title and freshness; do not add meta commentary, captions, repeated headings, forms, or action buttons.
- Publishing: after writing the file, call `visualise:publish_widget` — it validates and returns errors you can fix in the same run.
{{- if .Published}}
Current widget: version {{.Version}}, title {{printf "%q" .Title}}{{if .SizeHint}}, size {{.SizeHint}}{{end}}.
{{- if .LastError}}
Runtime error reported by the board since the last publish (fix it this run): {{.LastError}}
{{- end}}
